\par \plain \f1\b\fs18 Lynx Users Guide v2.8.7
\par \plain \f1\fs18 Lynx is a fully-featured\~\plain \f1\i\fs18 World Wide Web\plain \f1\fs18 \~(\plain \f1\i\fs18 WWW\plain \f1\fs18 ) client for users running cursor-addressable, character-cell display devices (e.g., vt100 terminals, vt100 emulators running on PCs or Macs, or any other character-cell display). It will display\~\plain \f1\i\fs18 Hypertext Markup Language\plain \f1\fs18 \~(\plain \f1\i\fs18 HTML\plain \f1\fs18 ) documents containing links to files on the local system, as well as files on remote systems running\~\plain \f1\i\fs18 http\plain \f1\fs18 ,\~\plain \f1\i\fs18 gopher\plain \f1\fs18 ,\~\plain \f1\i\fs18 ftp\plain \f1\fs18 ,\~\plain \f1\i\fs18 wais\plain \f1\fs18 ,\~\plain \f1\i\fs18 nntp\plain \f1\fs18 ,\~\plain \f1\i\fs18 finger\plain \f1\fs18 , or\~\plain \f1\i\fs18 cso\plain \f1\fs18 /\plain \f1\i\fs18 ph\plain \f1\fs18 /\plain \f1\i\fs18 qi\plain \f1\fs18 \~servers, and services accessible via logins to\~\plain \f1\i\fs18 telnet\plain \f1\fs18 ,\~\plain \f1\i\fs18 tn3270\plain \f1\fs18 or\~\plain \f1\i\fs18 rlogin\plain \f1\fs18 \~accounts (see\~\plain \f1\ul\fs18\cf1 URL Schemes Supported by Lynx\plain \f1\fs18 ).\~\plain \f1\ul\fs18\cf1 Current\plain \f1\fs18 \~versions of Lynx run on Unix, VMS, Windows3.x/9x/NT, 386DOS and OS/2 EMX.
\par Lynx can be used to access information on the\~\plain \f1\i\fs18 WWW\plain \f1\fs18 , or to build information systems intended primarily for local access. For example, Lynx has been used to build several\~\plain \f1\i\fs18 Campus Wide Information Systems\plain \f1\fs18 \~(\plain \f1\i\fs18 CWIS\plain \f1\fs18 ). In addition, Lynx can be used to build systems isolated within a single LAN.
